          "vnum": 1978,
          "name": "Steps Below a Clearing",
          "description": "Mold and lichen cling to a twisting arrangement of stones which form steps beneath a crumbling building. Insects squirm and chitter among the soil and roots at your sides of this passage into the earth. Up above is a crumbling ruin and a small doorway leading into an open clearing surrounded by trees.",
