          "vnum": 1984,
          "name": "East Cormanthus Trail",
          "description": "Staves of petrified wood mark the end of a road and the start of a trail into the eastern hills by Cormanthus. Atop some of the staves are the rotting skulls of semi-human creatures. The trail leads east, while the road offers passage to the southwest.",
