          "vnum": 1987,
          "name": "Cormanthus Hills",
          "description": "A well worn footpath leads south and east here among the hills above Cormanthus. To the southwest lay the remains of the village, while traces of a separate ruin are visible here among the hills as well. Skull-topped spears line the trail as markers to the east.",
