        "1988": {
          "vnum": 1988,
          "name": "Cormanthus Hills",
          "description": "The trail turns here offering passage downward to the west, and deeper into the hills to the southeast, where the remains of a large structure are slowly being reclaimed by time and decay. The gnarled, dry branches of two ancient and long- petrified trees tangle with one another here at the trail's southeastern pass.",
